1. Definitions

"Software" means the Exodus software, including its source code, build logic,
tools, scripts, and related materials distributed under this License.

"Covered Product" means any software product, service, platform, internal
system, or deliverable that is developed, built, compiled, generated,
packaged, analyzed, or materially enabled through use of the Software.

"Commercial Use" means any use of the Software or any Covered Product for
direct or indirect commercial advantage, private monetary compensation,
internal business operations, consulting delivery, hosted services, SaaS,
licensing, subscription access, or paid support. For the avoidance of doubt,
internal enterprise use counts as Commercial Use even if no external sale or
external distribution occurs.

"Non-Commercial Use" means personal, hobby, educational, academic, research,
or evaluation use that is not part of revenue-generating or commercial
business activity.

"Revenue" means gross revenue, without deduction for costs, taxes, fees,
refunds, or expenses, attributable to Covered Products during a calendar year.

"Legal Entity" means the individual, company, organization, or other legal
person using the Software.

"Threshold" means EUR 100,000 in annual Revenue from Covered Products.

"Commercial License Fee" means EUR 10,000 per calendar year.

2. License Grant

Subject to the terms of this License, you are granted a non-exclusive,
non-transferable, revocable license to use, copy, modify, and distribute the
Software in source or compiled form.

3. Free Use Cases

You may use the Software without payment if either of the following applies:

1. Your use is Non-Commercial Use.
2. Your Commercial Use does not cause the Revenue of your Legal Entity from
   Covered Products to exceed the Threshold during the applicable calendar
   year.

4. Commercial Threshold Obligation

If the Revenue of your Legal Entity from Covered Products exceeds the
Threshold in any calendar year, then continued Commercial Use of the Software
in that calendar year and each subsequent calendar year requires payment of
the Commercial License Fee.

The Commercial License Fee is due once per calendar year per Legal Entity,
unless the Licensor offers a different written commercial agreement.

Payment is due within thirty (30) days after written notice from the
Licensor. Payment shall be made via PayPal to n.ehrhardt88@gmail.com, unless
the Licensor provides different written payment instructions.

5. Distribution

You may distribute the Software, with or without modifications, provided that:

1. You include this License with any distribution.
2. You retain all copyright, attribution, and license notices.
3. You clearly mark modified versions as modified.
4. You do not represent your version as the original Software without
   permission.

6. No Open Source Representation

This License is not intended to be an open source license as defined by the
Open Source Definition published by the Open Source Initiative.

7. Payment Requirement After Threshold

If you exceed the Threshold and do not pay the Commercial License Fee, your
license for Commercial Use automatically terminates after thirty (30) days
written notice from the licensor, unless the required fee is paid within that
cure period.

Termination under this section does not affect any separate rights for
Non-Commercial Use.

8. Audit and Records

Upon reasonable written notice, and no more than once per calendar year, the
Licensor may request a written compliance statement and records reasonably
sufficient to verify whether the Threshold has been exceeded.

You are not required to disclose unrelated confidential technical information,
but you must provide sufficient revenue and usage information to determine
compliance with this License.

